verbs.description: outlean (third-person singular simple present outleans, present participle outleaning, simple past and past participle outleant or outleaned)

examples: And so, between those populous rough hands / Raised in the sun, Duke Leopold outleant, / And took the patriot's oath.

entries.meaning: (transitive) To lean further than; surpass in leaning.
examples: On the home stretch, the leader was gone, but there were five or six other guys who were within a few yards of each other for second place. I went outside on the last turn, with a Dave Wottle move, and I outleaned the others at the finish.
